data.description: Tonight: Increasing clouds, with a low around 51. Light and variable wind.

Friday: Rain likely after 11am.  Mostly cloudy, with a high near 59. South wind 14 to 18 mph, with gusts as high as 24 mph.  Chance of precipitation is 70%. New precipitation amounts of less than a tenth of an inch possible.

Friday Night: Showers likely, mainly before 11pm.  Mostly cloudy, with a low around 53. South southeast wind around 10 mph.  Chance of precipitation is 60%. New precipitation amounts of less than a tenth of an inch possible.
Saturday: A 30 percent chance of showers, mainly before 11am.  Mostly cloudy, with a high near 60. South southeast wind around 14 mph, with gusts as high as 18 mph.

Saturday Night: A slight chance of showers before 11pm, then a chance of rain, mainly after 5am.  Mostly cloudy, with a low around 54. South southeast wind 6 to 10 mph.  Chance of precipitation is 30%.
Sunday: Rain likely, mainly after 11am.  Cloudy, with a high near 60. Chance of precipitation is 60%. New precipitation amounts between a tenth and quarter of an inch possible.
Sunday Night: Rain. The rain could be heavy at times.  Low around 53. Chance of precipitation is 90%.
Monday: A chance of showers.  Partly sunny, with a high near 58.
Monday Night: Partly cloudy, with a low around 50.
